A women's lobby group has challenged President Uhuru Kenyatta to respect the two-thirds gender rule in the selection of his Cabinet.
 Federation of Women Lawyers (Fida) chairperson Josephine Mong’are (pictured) said the President should not ignore the Constitution he swore to obey and protect. 
 ALSO READ:

Co-operative bank group CEO to receive presidential award

 “The two-thirds gender rule is enshrined in our Constitution,” said Ms Mong'are.





